# Python program to find if x is a
# perfect square.

import math


def isPerfectSquare(x):

	#if x >= 0,
	if(x >= 0):
		sr = math.sqrt(x)
		# sqrt function returns floating value so we have to convert it into integer
		#return boolean T/F
		return ((sr*sr) == float(x))
	return false

# Driver code


x = 2502
if (isPerfectSquare(x)):
	print("Yes")
else:
	print("No")
